		<longTitle>Instead of original sin, think origin of sin</longTitle>
		<description>Most Christians know the story of the fall in Genesis as the act of disobedience that is the original sin. What if, instead, the story is about the origin of sin? </description>
		</head>
	<body>
		<outline text="Origin of Sin Rather than Original Sin">
			<outline text="The standard Christian explanation for why there is evil in the world: Original Sin" created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:14:18 GMT"/>
			<outline text="Known as an act of either disobedience or giving in to temptation" created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:15:44 GMT"/>
			<outline text="The problem with this thinking is that it makes sin something that we can either do or not do, rather than a condition of who we are." created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:16:37 GMT"/>
			<outline text="What if instead of thinking of the story of the fall in Genesis as about something that Adam and Eve did, we thought about it as a revelation of us, of God, and our relationship? " created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:17:32 GMT">
				<outline text="My way of thinking about this is as the origin of sin rather than the original sin" created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:19:48 GMT"/>
				<outline text="So, what is sin and how did it begin? " created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:20:28 GMT"/>
				<outline text="Sin is seeing ourselves apart from God and apart from each other" created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:20:55 GMT"/>
				<outline text="The origin of sin is the self awareness that comes at a young age that makes us see ourselves as unique and apart of each other" created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:21:55 GMT"/>
				</outline>
			<outline text="The label we use for the origin of sin today is racism" created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:24:42 GMT">
				<outline text="Have you ever wondered why racism seems impossible to overcome? " created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:25:31 GMT"/>
				<outline text="We we always struggle with racism as long as well continue to fail to see it for what it is, the origin of sin" created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:26:09 GMT"/>
				</outline>
			<outline text="We often think about original sin in the context of why things are the way they are today. What about how things were supposed to be from the beginning? What was then, and still is, God's desire? " created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:27:13 GMT">
				<outline text="The creation story in Genesis describes a scene in which God walked with Adam and Eve. He was present." created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:28:56 GMT"/>
				<outline text="Revelation describes a New Jerusalem and a return God being with his people" created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:29:58 GMT"/>
				<outline text="It seems to me God's desire is to be with amongst us, really present" created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:30:36 GMT"/>
				<outline text="Jesus prayed that his followers be as one as he and the Father were one" created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:31:36 GMT"/>
				<outline text="At-one-ment rather than Atonement" created="Sat, 09 Jul 2016 21:31:57 GMT"/>
				</outline>
			</outline>
		</body>
